<document> 

  <properties>
    <title>Launch analysis in hadoop mode</title>
    <author email="jourdren@biologie.ens.fr">Laurent Jourdren</author> 
  </properties> 



  <body>
  
    <section name="Launch analysis in hadoop mode">

      <p>This command launch Eoulsan in hadoop mode. First, the data is upload on the hadoop cluster and then analysis is launched.</p>  

      <ul>
         <li><b>Command name</b>: hadoopexec</li>
         <li><b>Mandatory parameters</b>:
	<table>
		<tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Value</th><th>Description</th></tr>
		<tr><td>parameter path</td><td>string</td><td>The path to parameter file to use</td></tr>
		<tr><td>design path</td><td>string</td><td>The path path design file to use</td></tr>
	</table>
        </li>
	<br/>
         <li><b>Optional parameters</b>:
	<table>
		<tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Value</th><th>Description</th></tr>
		<tr><td>-d</td><td>string</td><td>The description of the analysis</td></tr>
		<tr><td>-upload</td><td>none</td><td>Only upload data to hdfs</td></tr>
	</table>
        </li>
	<br/>
        <li><b>Usage</b>:
<source>
$ eoulsan.sh hadoopexec -d 'my test' param.xml design.txt hdfs://master.example.com/test
</source>

</li>
        
       </ul>
      
    </section>


  </body>
  
</document>
